  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prince Sultan bin Abdul Aziz Al Saud&apos;s contribution to the improvement of the presence of the Arabic language in UNESCO</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">At the 20th session of the General Conference, a resolution was adopted requesting the Director-General &quot;to take the measures needed to give Arabic the same status in UNESCO as the other more widely used working languages&quot; and &quot;to plan concrete action to achieve this&quot;. Since then, efforts have indeed been made to broaden the use of Arabic, financed in particular through the donation of $1 million from HRH Prince Sultan bin Abdul Aziz Al Saud. The recent donation of a further $2m means that UNESCO can envisage the possibility of a long-term impact for the Arabic language.</narrative>
  </description>
